{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":911,"text":"My son and the iPhone\nwere born three weeks apart"},{"time":4751,"text":"in June 2007."},{"time":7573,"text":"So while those early adopters\nwere lined up outside,"},{"time":10940,"text":"waiting to get their hands\non this amazing new gadget,"},{"time":13889,"text":"I was stuck at home\nwith my hands full of something else"},{"time":17857,"text":"that was sending out\nconstant notifications --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20127,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21984,"text":"a miserable, colicky baby"},{"time":24620,"text":"who would only sleep in a moving stroller\nwith complete silence."},{"time":30357,"text":"I literally was walking\n10 to 15 miles a day,"},{"time":33391,"text":"and the baby weight came off."},{"time":34990,"text":"That part was great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36615,"text":"But man, was I bored."},{"time":39397,"text":"Before motherhood, I had been a journalist"},{"time":41573,"text":"who rushed off when the Concorde crashed."},{"time":44164,"text":"I was one of the first\npeople into Belgrade"},{"time":46609,"text":"when there was a revolution in Serbia."},{"time":49134,"text":"Now, I was exhausted."},{"time":52366,"text":"This walking went on for weeks."},{"time":55266,"text":"It was only until about three months in\nthat something shifted, though."},{"time":60733,"text":"As I pounded the pavement,"},{"time":62844,"text":"my mind started to wander, too."},{"time":66031,"text":"I began imagining what I would do\nwhen I finally did sleep again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70305,"text":"So the colic did fade,"},{"time":72337,"text":"and I finally got an iPhone"},{"time":75160,"text":"and I put all those hours\nof wandering into action."},{"time":78079,"text":"I created my dream job\nhosting a public radio show."},{"time":82019,"text":"So there was no more\nrushing off to war zones,"},{"time":84203,"text":"but thanks to my new smartphone,"},{"time":86129,"text":"I could be a mother and a journalist."},{"time":88424,"text":"I could be on the playground\nand on Twitter at the same time."},{"time":93721,"text":"Yeah, well, when I thought that,"},{"time":95496,"text":"when the technology came in and took over,"},{"time":97567,"text":"that is when I hit a wall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100356,"text":"So, I want you to picture this:"},{"time":102590,"text":"you host a podcast, and you have to prove"},{"time":104868,"text":"that the investment\nof precious public radio dollars in you"},{"time":108312,"text":"is worth it."},{"time":109512,"text":"My goal was to increase\nmy audience size tenfold."},{"time":113781,"text":"So one day, I sat down to brainstorm,"},{"time":116269,"text":"as you do,"},{"time":117569,"text":"and I came up barren."},{"time":119562,"text":"This was different\nthan writer's block, right?"},{"time":121757,"text":"It wasn't like there was something there\nwaiting to be unearthed."},{"time":124856,"text":"There was just nothing."},{"time":126304,"text":"And so I started to think back:"},{"time":127806,"text":"When was the last time\nI actually had a good idea?"},{"time":130597,"text":"Yeah, it was when I was pushing\nthat damn stroller."},{"time":134052,"text":"Now all the cracks in my day\nwere filled with phone time."},{"time":137485,"text":"I checked the headlines\nwhile I waited for my latte."},{"time":141034,"text":"I updated my calendar\nwhile I was sitting on the couch."},{"time":145130,"text":"Texting turned every spare moment"},{"time":147579,"text":"into a chance to show to my coworkers\nand my dear husband"},{"time":150892,"text":"what a responsive person I was,"},{"time":153518,"text":"or at least it was a chance to find\nanother perfect couch"},{"time":156427,"text":"for my page on Pinterest."},{"time":159009,"text":"I realized that I was never bored."},{"time":161848,"text":"And anyway, don't only\nboring people get bored?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165208,"text":"But then I started to wonder:"},{"time":166614,"text":"What actually happens to us\nwhen we get bored?"},{"time":168900,"text":"Or, more importantly: What happens to us\nif we never get bored?"},{"time":173101,"text":"And what could happen if we got rid of\nthis human emotion entirely?"},{"time":178076,"text":"I started talking to neuroscientists\nand cognitive psychologists,"},{"time":182351,"text":"and what they told me was fascinating."},{"time":185300,"text":"It turns out that when you get bored,"},{"time":187117,"text":"you ignite a network in your brain\ncalled the \"default mode.\""},{"time":191225,"text":"So our body, it goes on autopilot\nwhile we're folding the laundry"},{"time":196108,"text":"or we're walking to work,"},{"time":197499,"text":"but actually that is when our brain\ngets really busy."},{"time":200484,"text":"Here's boredom researcher Dr. Sandi Mann."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204261,"text":"(Audio) Dr. Sandi Mann:\nOnce you start daydreaming"},{"time":206634,"text":"and allow your mind to really wander,"},{"time":208474,"text":"you start thinking a little bit\nbeyond the conscious,"},{"time":211057,"text":"a little bit into the subconscious,"},{"time":212804,"text":"which allows sort of different\nconnections to take place."},{"time":216000,"text":"It's really awesome, actually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217514,"text":"Manoush Zomorodi: Totally awesome, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":220044,"text":"So this is my brain in an fMRI,"},{"time":222271,"text":"and I learned that in the default mode\nis when we connect disparate ideas,"},{"time":226248,"text":"we solve some of our most\nnagging problems,"},{"time":228782,"text":"and we do something called\n\"autobiographical planning.\""},{"time":231847,"text":"This is when we look back at our lives,"},{"time":233766,"text":"we take note of the big moments,\nwe create a personal narrative,"},{"time":236989,"text":"and then we set goals"},{"time":238521,"text":"and we figure out what steps\nwe need to take to reach them."},{"time":241662,"text":"But now we chill out on the couch\nalso while updating a Google Doc"},{"time":246135,"text":"or replying to email."},{"time":248079,"text":"We call it \"getting shit done,\""},{"time":250631,"text":"but here's what neuroscientist\nDr. Daniel Levitin says"},{"time":253693,"text":"we're actually doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255690,"text":"(Audio) Dr. Daniel Levitin:\nEvery time you shift your attention"},{"time":258771,"text":"from one thing to another,"},{"time":260107,"text":"the brain has to engage\na neurochemical switch"},{"time":262859,"text":"that uses up nutrients in the brain\nto accomplish that."},{"time":266114,"text":"So if you're attempting to multitask,"},{"time":268557,"text":"you know, doing four\nor five things at once,"},{"time":270904,"text":"you're not actually doing\nfour or five things at once,"},{"time":273469,"text":"because the brain doesn't work that way."},{"time":275418,"text":"Instead, you're rapidly shifting\nfrom one thing to the next,"},{"time":278293,"text":"depleting neural resources as you go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280360,"text":"(Audio) MZ: So switch, switch, switch,\nyou're using glucose, glucose, glucose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284171,"text":"(Audio) DL: Exactly right, and we have\na limited supply of that stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287512,"text":"MZ: A decade ago, we shifted\nour attention at work"},{"time":289945,"text":"every three minutes."},{"time":291229,"text":"Now we do it every 45 seconds,"},{"time":294146,"text":"and we do it all day long."},{"time":296007,"text":"The average person checks email\n74 times a day,"},{"time":299367,"text":"and switches tasks on their computer"},{"time":301678,"text":"566 times a day."},{"time":305598,"text":"I discovered all this\ntalking to professor of informatics,"},{"time":309123,"text":"Dr. Gloria Mark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311307,"text":"(Audio) Dr. Gloria Mark: So we find\nthat when people are stressed,"},{"time":314877,"text":"they tend to shift\ntheir attention more rapidly."},{"time":318072,"text":"We also found, strangely enough,"},{"time":320335,"text":"that the shorter the amount of sleep\nthat a person gets,"},{"time":326059,"text":"the more likely they are\nto check Facebook."},{"time":328179,"text":"So we're in this vicious, habitual cycle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332245,"text":"MZ: But could this cycle be broken?"},{"time":334367,"text":"What would happen\nif we broke this vicious cycle?"},{"time":338667,"text":"Maybe my listeners could help me find out."},{"time":343461,"text":"What if we reclaimed\nthose cracks in our day?"},{"time":346596,"text":"Could it help us\njump-start our creativity?"},{"time":351222,"text":"We called the project\n\"Bored and Brilliant.\""},{"time":356264,"text":"And I expected, you know,\na couple hundred people to play along,"},{"time":359337,"text":"but thousands of people\nstarted signing up."},{"time":362438,"text":"And they told me the reason\nthey were doing it"},{"time":364634,"text":"was because they were worried\nthat their relationship with their phone"},{"time":368072,"text":"had grown kind of ...\n\"codependent,\" shall we say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372264,"text":"(Audio) Man: The relationship\nbetween a baby and its teddy bear"},{"time":375959,"text":"or a baby and its binky"},{"time":377798,"text":"or a baby that wants its mother's cradle"},{"time":381100,"text":"when it's done with being held\nby a stranger --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384146,"text":"(Laughs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":385222,"text":"that's the relationship\nbetween me and my phone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388198,"text":"(Audio) Woman: I think of my phone\nlike a power tool:"},{"time":390997,"text":"extremely useful, but dangerous\nif I'm not handling it properly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394930,"text":"(Audio) Woman 2:\nIf I don't pay close attention,"},{"time":397232,"text":"I'll suddenly realize\nthat I've lost an hour of time"},{"time":399709,"text":"doing something totally mindless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401724,"text":"MZ: OK, but to really measure\nany improvement,"},{"time":404051,"text":"we needed data, right?"},{"time":405496,"text":"Because that's what we do these days."},{"time":407711,"text":"So we partnered with some apps\nthat would measure how much time"},{"time":410873,"text":"we were spending every day on our phone."},{"time":412989,"text":"If you're thinking it's ironic"},{"time":414490,"text":"that I asked people\nto download another app"},{"time":416563,"text":"so that they would spend\nless time on their phones:"},{"time":419110,"text":"yeah, but you gotta meet people\nwhere they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421441,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":422967,"text":"So before challenge week,"},{"time":424769,"text":"we were averaging two hours\na day on our phones"},{"time":427661,"text":"and 60 pickups,"},{"time":429393,"text":"you know, like, a quick check,\ndid I get a new email?"},{"time":432144,"text":"Here's what Tina, a student\nat Bard College,"},{"time":434378,"text":"discovered about herself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436732,"text":"(Audio) Tina: So far, I've been spending"},{"time":438733,"text":"between 150 and 200 minutes\non my phone per day,"},{"time":442219,"text":"and I've been picking up my phone\n70 to 100 times per day."},{"time":446368,"text":"And it's really concerning,"},{"time":448068,"text":"because that's so much time\nthat I could have spent"},{"time":450526,"text":"doing something more productive,\nmore creative, more towards myself,"},{"time":454402,"text":"because when I'm on my phone,\nI'm not doing anything important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457384,"text":"MZ: Like Tina, people were starting\nto observe their own behavior."},{"time":460753,"text":"They were getting ready\nfor challenge week."},{"time":463351,"text":"And that Monday,"},{"time":465149,"text":"they started to wake up\nto instructions in their inbox,"},{"time":468048,"text":"an experiment to try."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470065,"text":"Day one:"},{"time":471640,"text":"\"Put it in your pocket.\""},{"time":473249,"text":"Take that phone out of your hand."},{"time":475565,"text":"See if you can eliminate the reflex\nto check it all day long,"},{"time":478564,"text":"just for a day."},{"time":480082,"text":"And if this sounds easy,"},{"time":481587,"text":"you haven't tried it."},{"time":482860,"text":"Here's listener Amanda Itzko."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484944,"text":"(Audio) Amanda Itzko:\nI am absolutely itching."},{"time":488708,"text":"I feel a little bit crazy,"},{"time":491188,"text":"because I have noticed\nthat I pick up my phone"},{"time":495896,"text":"when I'm just walking\nfrom one room to another,"},{"time":499828,"text":"getting on the elevator,"},{"time":501118,"text":"and even -- and this is the part\nthat I am really embarrassed"},{"time":504919,"text":"to actually say out loud --"},{"time":506930,"text":"in the car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508381,"text":"MZ: Yikes."},{"time":509578,"text":"Yeah, well, but as Amanda learned,"},{"time":511271,"text":"this itching feeling\nis not actually her fault."},{"time":514678,"text":"That is exactly the behavior\nthat the technology is built to trigger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519053,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":523737,"text":"I mean, right?"},{"time":525807,"text":"Here's former Google designer,\nTristan Harris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529309,"text":"(Audio) Tristan Harris: If I'm Facebook\nor I'm Netflix or I'm Snapchat,"},{"time":532709,"text":"I have literally a thousand engineers"},{"time":534591,"text":"whose job is to get\nmore attention from you."},{"time":537186,"text":"I'm very good at this,"},{"time":538749,"text":"and I don't want you to ever stop."},{"time":540489,"text":"And you know, the CEO\nof Netflix recently said,"},{"time":542735,"text":"\"Our biggest competitors\nare Facebook, YouTube and sleep.\""},{"time":545981,"text":"I mean, so there's a million places\nto spend your attention,"},{"time":549279,"text":"but there's a war going on to get it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551230,"text":"MZ: I mean, you know the feeling:"},{"time":552952,"text":"that amazing episode\nof \"Transparent\" ends,"},{"time":555105,"text":"and then the next one starts playing"},{"time":556881,"text":"so you're like, eh, OK fine,\nI'll just stay up and watch it."},{"time":559805,"text":"Or the LinkedIn progress bar\nsays you are this close"},{"time":562908,"text":"to having the perfect profile,"},{"time":565088,"text":"so you add a little more\npersonal information."},{"time":568220,"text":"As one UX designer told me,"},{"time":570238,"text":"the only people who refer\nto their customers as \"users\""},{"time":573535,"text":"are drug dealers and technologists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575627,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577007,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":583379,"text":"And users, as we know,\nare worth a lot of money."},{"time":586827,"text":"Here's former Facebook\nproduct manager and author,"},{"time":590261,"text":"Antonio García Martínez."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593547,"text":"(Audio) Antonio García Martínez:\nThe saying is, if any product is free"},{"time":596889,"text":"then you're the product;\nyour attention is the product."},{"time":599514,"text":"But what is your attention worth?"},{"time":601112,"text":"That's why literally every time\nyou load a page,"},{"time":603389,"text":"not just on Facebook or any app,"},{"time":604953,"text":"there's an auction being held instantly,\nbillions of times a day,"},{"time":608048,"text":"for exactly how much\nthat one ad impression cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610386,"text":"MZ: By the way, the average person\nwill spend two years of their life"},{"time":613697,"text":"on Facebook."},{"time":615222,"text":"So, back to challenge week."},{"time":616788,"text":"Immediately, we saw\nsome creativity kick in."},{"time":620224,"text":"Here's New Yorker Lisa Alpert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622773,"text":"(Audio) Lisa Alpert: I was bored, I guess."},{"time":624961,"text":"So I suddenly looked at the stairway\nthat went up to the top of the station,"},{"time":629590,"text":"and I thought, you know,"},{"time":631153,"text":"I had just come down that stairway,\nbut I could go back up"},{"time":634438,"text":"and then come back down\nand get a little cardio."},{"time":636947,"text":"So I did,"},{"time":638135,"text":"and then I had a little more time,\nso I did it again and I did it again,"},{"time":642000,"text":"and I did it 10 times."},{"time":643830,"text":"And I had a complete cardio workout."},{"time":646225,"text":"I got on that R train feeling\nkind of exhausted,"},{"time":648676,"text":"but, like, wow,\nthat had never occurred to me."},{"time":651364,"text":"How is that possible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":652783,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":653911,"text":"MZ: So creativity, I learned, means\ndifferent things to different people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657921,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":658945,"text":"But everyone found\nday three's challenge the hardest."},{"time":662522,"text":"It was called \"Delete that app.\""},{"time":664762,"text":"Take that app -- you know the one;"},{"time":666663,"text":"that one that always gets you,\nit sucks you in --"},{"time":669463,"text":"take it off your phone,"},{"time":670650,"text":"even if just for the day."},{"time":672062,"text":"I deleted the game Two Dots\nand nearly cried."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675348,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676418,"text":"Yeah, Two Dots players\nknow what I'm talking about."},{"time":678861,"text":"But my misery had good company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684374,"text":"(Audio) Man 2: This is Liam\nin Los Angeles,"},{"time":686650,"text":"and I deleted Twitter, Facebook,\nInstagram, Tumblr, Snapchat and Vine"},{"time":691507,"text":"from my phone"},{"time":692686,"text":"in one fell swoop."},{"time":694311,"text":"And it was kind of an embarrassingly\nemotional experience at first."},{"time":698976,"text":"It felt weirdly lonely\nto look at that lock screen"},{"time":702872,"text":"with no new notifications on it."},{"time":705253,"text":"But I really liked deciding for myself"},{"time":708325,"text":"when to think about or access\nmy social networks,"},{"time":711741,"text":"not giving my phone the power\nto decide that for me."},{"time":715739,"text":"So thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716941,"text":"(Audio) Woman 3: Deleting the Twitter app\nwas very sad,"},{"time":719656,"text":"and I feel I maybe, over the last year\nwhen I've been on Twitter,"},{"time":723218,"text":"have developed an addiction to it,"},{"time":724862,"text":"and this \"Bored and Brilliant\" challenge\nhas really made me realize it."},{"time":728274,"text":"After a brief period of really horrible\nwithdrawal feeling,"},{"time":731430,"text":"like lack-of-caffeine headache,"},{"time":733423,"text":"I now feel lovely."},{"time":735023,"text":"I had a lovely dinner with my family,"},{"time":736858,"text":"and I hope to continue this structured use\nof these powerful tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741557,"text":"(Audio) Woman 4: I don't have\nthat guilty gut feeling"},{"time":744080,"text":"I have when I know\nI'm wasting time on my phone."},{"time":746399,"text":"Maybe I'll have to start giving myself\nchallenges and reminders like this"},{"time":749925,"text":"every morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751101,"text":"MZ: I mean, yes, this was progress."},{"time":752818,"text":"I could not wait to see\nwhat the numbers said"},{"time":755309,"text":"at the end of that week."},{"time":758151,"text":"But when the data came in,"},{"time":760078,"text":"it turned out that we had cut down,"},{"time":762375,"text":"on average,"},{"time":763637,"text":"just six minutes --"},{"time":765927,"text":"from 120 minutes a day on our phones"},{"time":768761,"text":"to 114."},{"time":771654,"text":"Yeah. Whoop-de-do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773297,"text":"So I went back to the scientists\nfeeling kind of low,"},{"time":777031,"text":"and they just laughed at me,"},{"time":778535,"text":"and they said, you know,\nchanging people's behavior"},{"time":780990,"text":"in such a short time period"},{"time":782547,"text":"was ridiculously ambitious,"},{"time":784798,"text":"and actually what you've achieved\nis far beyond what we thought possible."},{"time":790041,"text":"Because more important than the numbers,\nwere the people's stories."},{"time":793901,"text":"They felt empowered."},{"time":795567,"text":"Their phones had been transformed"},{"time":798230,"text":"from taskmasters"},{"time":799983,"text":"back into tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802708,"text":"And actually, I found what\nthe young people said most intriguing."},{"time":806682,"text":"Some of them told me"},{"time":807861,"text":"that they didn't recognize\nsome of the emotions"},{"time":810147,"text":"that they felt during challenge week,"},{"time":811966,"text":"because, if you think about it,"},{"time":813477,"text":"if you have never known life\nwithout connectivity,"},{"time":816465,"text":"you may never have experienced boredom."},{"time":819471,"text":"And there could be consequences."},{"time":821561,"text":"Researchers at USC have found --\nthey're studying teenagers"},{"time":825014,"text":"who are on social media\nwhile they're talking to their friends"},{"time":827998,"text":"or they're doing homework,"},{"time":829308,"text":"and two years down the road,\nthey are less creative and imaginative"},{"time":833147,"text":"about their own personal futures"},{"time":835025,"text":"and about solving societal problems,\nlike violence in their neighborhoods."},{"time":839691,"text":"And we really need this next generation"},{"time":842320,"text":"to be able to focus on some big problems:"},{"time":844570,"text":"climate change, economic disparity,"},{"time":847038,"text":"massive cultural differences."},{"time":849662,"text":"No wonder CEOs in an IBM survey"},{"time":852407,"text":"identified creativity as the number one\nleadership competency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858214,"text":"OK, here's the good news, though:"},{"time":859906,"text":"In the end, 20,000 people\ndid \"Bored and Brilliant\" that week."},{"time":863701,"text":"Ninety percent cut down on their minutes."},{"time":866157,"text":"Seventy percent got more time to think."},{"time":869051,"text":"People told me that they slept better."},{"time":871204,"text":"They felt happier."},{"time":872545,"text":"My favorite note was from a guy\nwho said he felt like he was waking up"},{"time":876193,"text":"from a mental hibernation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880141,"text":"Some personal data and some neuroscience"},{"time":882609,"text":"gave us permission\nto be offline a little bit more,"},{"time":885774,"text":"and a little bit of boredom\ngave us some clarity"},{"time":888741,"text":"and helped some of us set some goals."},{"time":892156,"text":"I mean, maybe constant connectivity"},{"time":894291,"text":"won't be cool in a couple of years."},{"time":898073,"text":"But meanwhile, teaching people,\nespecially kids,"},{"time":901655,"text":"how to use technology\nto improve their lives"},{"time":904806,"text":"and to self-regulate"},{"time":906245,"text":"needs to be part of digital literacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910685,"text":"So the next time you go\nto check your phone,"},{"time":913632,"text":"remember that if you don't decide\nhow you're going to use the technology,"},{"time":917728,"text":"the platforms will decide for you."},{"time":921013,"text":"And ask yourself:"},{"time":922618,"text":"What am I really looking for?"},{"time":924380,"text":"Because if it's to check email,\nthat's fine -- do it and be done."},{"time":928099,"text":"But if it's to distract yourself\nfrom doing the hard work"},{"time":930791,"text":"that comes with deeper thinking,"},{"time":933115,"text":"take a break,"},{"time":934547,"text":"stare out the window"},{"time":936667,"text":"and know that by doing nothing"},{"time":939536,"text":"you are actually being\nyour most productive and creative self."},{"time":944262,"text":"It might feel weird\nand uncomfortable at first,"},{"time":947009,"text":"but boredom truly can lead to brilliance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950394,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951570,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}